attrs.short-hed: Couch: 5K run provides humbling truth about fitness
attrs.subhead: Couch to 5K in one day is a perfect but painful barometer of one's conditioning
attrs.photo-hed: Couch: 5K run provides humbling truth about fitness
attrs.brief: Couch to 5K in one day is a perfect but painful barometer of one's conditioning
attrs.metadescription: LANSING — I ran the Capitol 5K in 31 minutes and 15 seconds Friday evening, finishing 10th in the ever-brutal Men's 35 to 39 age group. Never mind there were only 12 of us. In my defense, I was stuck behind a walker for the first few steps. I think I would have eclipsed 31 minutes otherwise.
attrs.byline: GRAHAM COUCH, FOR THE LANSING STATE JOURNAL
attrs.chatter: Couch to 5K in one day is a perfect but painful barometer of one's conditioning

attrs.subhead: Couch to 5K in one day is a perfect but painful barometer of one's conditioning
attrs.photo-hed: Couch: 5K run provides humbling truth about fitness
attrs.brief: Couch to 5K in one day is a perfect but painful barometer of one's conditioning
attrs.metadescription: LANSING — I ran the Capitol 5K in 31 minutes and 15 seconds Friday evening, finishing 10th in the ever-brutal Men's 35 to 39 age group. Never mind there were only 12 of us. In my defense, I was stuck behind a walker for the first few steps. I think I would have eclipsed 31 minutes otherwise.
attrs.byline: GRAHAM COUCH, FOR THE LANSING STATE JOURNAL

photo.caption: The 634-foot American Courage freighter heads towards Lake Superior through the Soo Locks on the St.Mary’s River in Sault Ste. Marie. The U.S. locks are run by the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers. Congress has authorized, but not funded, a new lock.
